descript.abstract: This shapefile contains names and locations of all non-sensitive Federal Facilities Section sites.
descript.purpose: This shapefile was developed to provide general reference locations of former and current Federal Facility sites within Missouri to the general public and other state and federal agencies.
descript.supplinf: The metadata content associated with this data set was reviewed by Michael Hill on 20080214. The metadata content review is intended to ensure that all of the required content is present. The components comprising the metadata document were reviewed by Michael Hill on 20080214. The metadata component review is intended to ensure that required metadata components are consistent and understandable to data consumers.

idinfo.accconst: This data set contains all non-sensitive Federal Facilities Section site locational data. This dataset does not contain all of the sites overseen by the Federal Facilities Section, the sites with sensitive locational data were excluded for security reasons. Acknowledgement of the Missouri Department of Natural Resources when using this data set is appreciated.

attracc.attraccr: Attribute accuracy of NORTHING and EASTING attributes are discussed in the horizontal positional accuracy report. Each SITENAME attribute was accuracy checked by comparison with known naming conventions and information provided by federal agencies.

dataqual.complete: This dataset contains locational data of former and current Federal Facilities Section sites within the state of Missouri for use by the general public or other state and federal agencies. This dataset excludes sensitive sites. Those sites that have a sensitive component and were excluded from this dataset are as follows: Air Force Plant #65, Camp Clark, Fort Crowder - Formerly Used Defense Site (FUDS), Fort Leonard Wood Maneuver Area, Fort Leonard Wood Satellite Prisoner Of War (POW) Camp, Fort Leonard Wood, Formerly Utilized Sites Remedial Action Program (FUSRAP) St. Louis Downtown Site (SLDS) Vicinity Properties, Jefferson Barracks Air National Guard Base, Kansas City Federal Center GSA, Kansas City Federal Center Landfill, Lake City Army Ammunition Plant, Mallinckrodt C-T, National Imagery & Mapping Agency (Formerly Defense Mapping - 2nd St), Sedalia Army Air Field Division Training Area, St. Louis Ordnance Plant Hanley Area, Weldon Spring Ordnance Works, Whiteman Air Force Base. For information on these sites please contact Federal Facilities Section at (573) 751-3907.

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal accuracy is tested by manual comparison of source with hard copy printouts and/or display of data using Digital Orthophoto Quarter Quadrangle (DOQQ) files and Environmental Systems Research Institute (ESRI) ArcGIS software. Where possible, site information was verified and/or updated with Global Positioning System (GPS) instrumentation.

procstep.procdesc: The entirety of this shapefile was developed on-screen using "heads-up" digitizing in Environmental Systems Research Institute (ESRI) Arcview 8.3. Each feature was visually corrected by comparison with the paper maps of the site and the use of Digital Orthophoto Quarter Quadrangles (DOQQs) as base maps. On sites that do not submit site locational maps, the project manager collects a Global Positioning System (GPS) reading near the center of operation. This location is plotted on a DOQQ and the project manager and section Geographic Information Systems (GIS) coordinator verify the location is correct. Once all sites were topologically correct, they were attributed and a shapefile was created. Upon completion, a printed version of the location was examined and approved by both the site project manager and the section's GIS coordinator. The locational information was stored in the Federal Facilities Section GIS archive as a database file.
